claim: Flublok contains 45 micrograms (mcg) of HA per strain vs 15 mcg of HA per strain in a standard-dose influenza vaccine.
explanation: A table titled ‘Influenza vaccines — United States, 2023–24 influenza season,’ listing various vaccines (standard-dose egg-based IIV4, cell culture–based ccIIV4, and high-dose egg-based HD-IIV4), with columns for trade name, presentations, age indication, μg HA per dose for each vaccine virus, route, and mercury content. Visible entries include Afluria Quadrivalent, Fluarix Quadrivalent, FluLaval Quadrivalent, Fluzone Quadrivalent, Flucelvax Quadrivalent, and Fluzone High-Dose Quadrivalent. does not support the claim because the image does not include any data on Flublok or a 45 μg per strain formulation; it only shows standard-dose vaccines with 15 μg per strain and a high-dose vaccine with 60 μg total (15 μg per strain).
